816
00:31:42,920 --> 00:31:47,920
I stayed quiet because noise makes liars sloppy.

817
00:31:48,519 --> 00:31:52,560
She sits down, folds her hands.

818
00:31:54,000 --> 00:31:57,800
She says, come in, have a seat, close the door.

819
00:31:57,800 --> 00:32:00,160
Sure, yeah, I'll be right there.

820
00:32:00,160 --> 00:32:03,279
The sound of the party, which has kind of picked up,

821
00:32:03,279 --> 00:32:04,759
people have stopped giving speeches

822
00:32:04,759 --> 00:32:05,640
and there's more just like,

823
00:32:05,640 --> 00:32:08,039
shot, shot, shot, shot, shot, shot, shot.

824
00:32:09,000 --> 00:32:11,519
You close the door and which dims

825
00:32:11,519 --> 00:32:14,039
everything happening outside and says,

826
00:32:14,039 --> 00:32:19,039
your father believes he has simply been unlucky in love.

827
00:32:21,159 --> 00:32:24,799
Oh, well, we both know that's not the case though, right?

828
00:32:24,799 --> 00:32:26,039
No, of course not.

829
00:32:26,039 --> 00:32:28,960
It's not that he chooses poorly

830
00:32:28,960 --> 00:32:32,240
or that hearts are fragile things.

831
00:32:33,519 --> 00:32:36,639
The small humorless smile comes across her

832
00:32:36,800 --> 00:32:41,800
very stoic face and that is not what happened.

833
00:32:43,680 --> 00:32:46,440
She noticed you sat a little further away from her

834
00:32:46,440 --> 00:32:49,920
and she gets up and pulls her chair closer to you.

835
00:32:50,840 --> 00:32:52,560
Not getting a threatening vibe,

836
00:32:52,560 --> 00:32:56,720
but she's coming over to you for certainty.

837
00:32:56,720 --> 00:33:01,720
She says, years ago, before you were grown,

838
00:33:02,440 --> 00:33:06,560
your father signed a document that he did not understand.

839
00:33:07,480 --> 00:33:08,480
I mean, I do not think that is the first

840
00:33:08,480 --> 00:33:10,599
and only time that has happened, but please continue.

841
00:33:10,599 --> 00:33:15,240
No, yes, it was a civic agreement.

842
00:33:15,240 --> 00:33:16,079
You're right.

843
00:33:16,079 --> 00:33:17,319
He has signed many of them.

844
00:33:18,279 --> 00:33:21,519
It was a consolidation of authority,

845
00:33:22,440 --> 00:33:26,319
something boring to him, you know, Harrison.

846
00:33:26,319 --> 00:33:27,159
Okay.

847
00:33:27,159 --> 00:33:29,759
Something men like him never read closely.

848
00:33:31,720 --> 00:33:35,200
She looks to you knowingly

849
00:33:36,759 --> 00:33:39,480
the words did not stay where he put them.

850
00:33:40,639 --> 00:33:45,639
They were taken, preserved, filed.

851
00:33:47,960 --> 00:33:50,399
I do a lot of filing in my job.

852
00:33:50,399 --> 00:33:53,200
Well, in my old, well, I didn't do it,

853
00:33:53,200 --> 00:33:55,279
but like I was around while it was done.

854
00:33:55,279 --> 00:33:57,839
So I'm with you so far.

855
00:33:57,839 --> 00:34:01,559
She lifts the brim of her hat, even removes it.

856
00:34:01,559 --> 00:34:03,079
So you can see her eyes.

857
00:34:04,000 --> 00:34:07,760
They were filed in the Weeping Archive.

858
00:34:07,760 --> 00:34:10,480
Oh shit, I've actually heard of that.

859
00:34:10,480 --> 00:34:15,280
Every marriage after that was not chaos.

860
00:34:15,280 --> 00:34:16,800
It was containment.

861
00:34:17,800 --> 00:34:20,800
Each wife placed near him by coincidence,

862
00:34:20,800 --> 00:34:23,640
by council, by recommendation.

863
00:34:23,640 --> 00:34:27,519
Families with scribes, record keepers,

864
00:34:27,519 --> 00:34:32,280
people who knew how to erase a just delay.

865
00:34:33,920 --> 00:34:36,639
He thought he was protecting himself.

866
00:34:36,639 --> 00:34:39,559
The Archive thought it was indexing him.

867
00:34:41,840 --> 00:34:44,799
That's why he forgets things that matter.

868
00:34:46,000 --> 00:34:48,920
That's why records vanish.

869
00:34:48,920 --> 00:34:51,639
And that's why Vintersmouth

870
00:34:51,639 --> 00:34:54,799
keeps surviving scandals it should not.

871
00:34:56,960 --> 00:35:01,279
Your father is not powerful, Kavlarananan.

872
00:35:01,279 --> 00:35:02,440
He is footnoted.

873
00:35:03,759 --> 00:35:05,039
She stands up.

874
00:35:07,079 --> 00:35:10,360
I waited to see what kind of man you were before telling you.

875
00:35:11,639 --> 00:35:15,519
Whether you could carry truth without turning it into a weapon.

876
00:35:17,159 --> 00:35:19,480
Now you know where to look.

877
00:35:20,960 --> 00:35:23,840
The Archive already knows who you are.

878
00:35:25,119 --> 00:35:27,239
She turns to leave.

879
00:35:27,239 --> 00:35:31,599
She opens the door and the sound of the party picks up again

880
00:35:31,679 --> 00:35:33,360
as the door opens.

881
00:35:33,360 --> 00:35:36,719
As she exits, she adds without turning back.

882
00:35:37,799 --> 00:35:41,759
If you ever read your father's name in ink that won't dry,

883
00:35:42,599 --> 00:35:45,559
don't touch the page.

884
00:35:48,759 --> 00:35:49,679
Okay, noted.

885
00:35:50,559 --> 00:35:53,599
She turns the corner.

886
00:35:53,599 --> 00:35:58,599
As you get up to follow her, she's gone down the hall.

887
00:35:58,759 --> 00:36:01,440
It's weird that every conversation I have with her is like this.

